    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-10-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="141" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d141">
                <head>No. 141.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Morton</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-10-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 1,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 358.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 403, of the 12th instant,
                        giving an account of the ceremonies which were observed on the occasion of
                        the unveiling of the statue of La Fayette at Le Puy, on the 6th of the
                        present month, has been, read with great interest.</p>
                <p>Your action in accepting the invitation to be present at the ceremonies as
                        the representative of this country is heartily approved by the President,
                        and he is gratified to learn that the event called forth so many warm
                        expressions of the good will of the people of France towards the Government
                        and citizens of the United States.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
